<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1500,2029]" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Tegmina and hind wings developed. Tegmina subcoriaceous, narrow and long, slightly exceeding metafemoral apices, sometimes by about fifth of its full length, apices broad circular; stigmatic arch in the middle, discoidal vein very distinct, approaching the radial vein near the apex; medial area with distinct median intercalary vein which is closer to anterior cubitus basally and closer to media apically, and have stridulating files; cubital area wider than medial area, with intercalary and irregular reticulate veins; cross-veins oblique to longitudinal veins in apical part of tegmen and arranged in zig-zag, cells parallelogrammic.</paragraph>
