<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1519,1544]" pageId="9" pageNumber="554">Remarks.</emphasis>
Uvarov (
<number box="[425,483,1519,1544]" pageId="9" pageNumber="554" value="1925.0">1925</number>
) discussed in his original description that “A remarkable feature of its pronotum is the notch of the median keel opposite the first sulcus; this is in the disagreement with generic diagnosis, but I am not at all sure whether this is not an individual abnormity. The highly characteristic reticulation of the elytra leaves no doubt as to correctness of generic assignment of the new species”. We examined the 
<typeStatus box="[1202,1261,1629,1653]" pageId="9" pageNumber="554">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zheng, 1981" authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Flatovertex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufotibialis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="554">Flatovertex rufotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and some additional materials identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Zheng, 1981" authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="1981" box="[772,1034,1663,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Flatovertex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufotibialis">
<emphasis box="[772,1034,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="554">Flatovertex rufotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Mao 
<emphasis box="[1135,1185,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="554">et al</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1200,1258,1664,1688]" pageId="9" pageNumber="554" value="2011.0">2011</number>
) and found that they highly agreed with each other morphologically except the notch of the median keel opposite the first sulcus in 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1735,1760]" pageId="9" pageNumber="554">holotype</typeStatus>
male of 
<taxonomicName box="[349,614,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Pternoscirta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchripes">
<emphasis box="[349,614,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="554">Pternoscirta pulchripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This result obviously confirmed Uvarov’s suspicion about the abnormal notch of the median keel of pronotum. Since no morphological difference was found between 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Pternoscirta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchripes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="554">Pternoscirta pulchripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Zheng, 1981" authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="1981" box="[339,607,1807,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Flatovertex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufotibialis">
<emphasis box="[339,607,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="554">Flatovertex rufotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we propose herein 
<taxonomicName authority="Zheng, 1981" authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="1981" box="[865,1134,1807,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Flatovertex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufotibialis">
<emphasis box="[865,1134,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="554">Flatovertex rufotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,416,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Pternoscirta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchripes">
<emphasis box="[151,416,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="554">Pternoscirta pulchripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
